name: The number of non-unitary prime divisors of the noncubefree numbers.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: Asymptotic mean: Limit_{m->oo} (1/m) * Sum_{k=1..m} a(k) = (zeta(3) * Sum_{p prime} (1/p^2) - Sum_{p prime} ((p-1)/(p^3-1))) / (zeta(3) - 1) = 1.21311144181724050823... .
mathematica: f[k_] := Module[{e = If[k == 1, {}, FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]]}, If[AnyTrue[e, # > 2 &], Count[e, _?(# > 1 &)], Nothing]]; Array[f, 600]
program: (PARI) list(kmax) = {my(e, is); for(k = 1, kmax, e = factor(k)[, 2]; is = 0; for(i = 1, #e, if(e[i] > 2, is = 1; break)); if(is, print1(#select(x -> x > 1, e), ", "))); }
author: _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 25 2025
